# heymeld.com environment variables
#
# Local dev:
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# Production — set in Cloudflare Pages:
#   dash.cloudflare.com → Workers & Pages → heymeld → Settings → Variables
#   (Must be prefixed PUBLIC_ to be readable at build time by Astro.)

# ── TelemetryDeck analytics ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# Meld Web app ID from dash.telemetrydeck.com.
# Separate from the iOS App ID to keep web + mobile signals segregated.
# If unset in local dev, the analytics script is simply not injected.
PUBLIC_TELEMETRYDECK_APP_ID=

# ── Deprecated ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# PUBLIC_API_BASE is no longer used. Earlier in the project, the waitlist
# form POSTed to `${PUBLIC_API_BASE}/api/waitlist/subscribe` on the Railway
# FastAPI backend. We later pivoted the waitlist onto a same-origin
# Cloudflare Pages Function at `functions/api/waitlist/subscribe.ts`
# backed by a Cloudflare D1 database.
#
# The form now POSTs to `/api/waitlist/subscribe` on the same origin as
# the site, eliminating the CORS round-trip and the Railway dependency
# entirely. The D1 binding is declared in `wrangler.toml`.
#
# If you ever need to repoint the form at a different backend, edit
# `src/components/WaitlistForm.astro` and change the `endpoint` const.
